# node-tar 6.2.1 -> 7.x : MAJOR bump of a BUILD-TIME-ONLY transitive dep.
#   Dependents in this tree: node-gyp, cacache, sqlite3 (native-build tooling).
#   The CVEs are arbitrary file write / overwrite / path-traversal during tar
#   EXTRACTION. The app never extracts untrusted archives at runtime; these
#   tools only unpack trusted npm-registry tarballs at build time. The only
#   fixes are in tar 7.x — forcing it (override) risks breaking native
#   compilation in the Docker builder, which can't be verified outside CI.
#   DEFERRED to a dedicated, tested follow-up (bump tar -> 7 + sqlite3/node-gyp
#   as needed; verify the image builds and the server + chat boot). Until then
#   these are accepted build-time risk, not runtime-reachable.
